system.base.Wet_attributes

type
class

Constructor

new(?iclass : String, ?i_id : String, ?style : String, ?title : String, ?valign : String, ?accesskey : String, ?tabindex : Int, ?xml_lang : String, ?nonw3c : String, ?i_lang : String, ?dir : String)
parameters
tclass The elements CSS class.
id The elements ID - this should be unique.
title A title hint for this element - shows as a hint in many browsers.
accesskey Used in forms only - this defines the key to press to access the control.
tabindex Used in forms only - alters how the tab key works.
xml_lang XML:LANG element - only applies to XHMTL doctypes
style A local style definition as - CLASS should be used in preference.
nonw3c a parameter (or string of parameters to pass to the element that are not available via a class/style)
lang A language element if required.
dir The dir element (LTR or RTL)
Creates a new attributes instance with none (!) or more of the attributes common to HTML elements. No checking is done on the integrity of the information as it might change outside of the program control. Non-suppored elments (or deprecated fields) can be added in the nonw3c variable.

Instance Methods

insert_attributes() : String

Inserts the instance-defined set of attributes. Attributes can be changed at run time through a dot.method
